person.note:
Author and journalist; contributed to Punch and other periodicals;
      wrote light dramatic pieces; foreign correspondent; wrote The Russians at Home (1861); wrote
      on musical history and criticism; editor of The Graphic. See ODNB.

LUCAS, JOHN TEMPLETON (eld. son of the preceding). _b._ London 1836;
     exhibited 7 landscapes at R.A., 13 at B.I. and 30 at Suffolk st. gallery 1859–76; his farce
     Browne the Martyr produced at Court theatre 20 Jany. 1872 and printed in Lacy’s acting edition
     of plays vol. xcvi; author of fairy tales entitled Prince Ubbely Bubble’s New story book 1871;
     and of Edwin Landseer 1873, memorial verses. _d._ Whitby, Sep. 1880.
